{In this workshop, I will present the Accelerated Dragon with the move 5.Nc3 and all sidelines on move 2 and 3. More or less, it covers the Sicilian. It is an excellent addition to the previous camp about Maroczy Bind. I structured the database in the following way: First, you will find the theoretical file, and immediately after it, I put model games without comments. At the end of the file, you will also find the excellent database for Accelerated Dragon by GM Salvador Alonso and GM Lorenzini. Let me briefly go through the variations:} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 (2. g3) (2. b3) (2. f4) (2. b4) (2. Be2 {are also covered}) (2. c3 {In the , beginning I start with the sidelines on the move 2. The most serious one is the Alapin Variation} {Where I suggested} d5 3. exd5 Qxd5 4. d4 Nc6 5. Nf3 Nf6 {The so-called "Two Knights" variation which has become very popular nowadays and I can't find any problems for Black}) (2. Nc3 {Is a severe move to which I dedicated one lecture. Here I analyze} Nc6 3. Bb5 (3. g3) (3. f4)) 2... Nc6 3. d4 ({The third lecture is about Rossolimo. This was a tough challenge, but I am pretty satisfied with the results.} 3. Bb5 {I choose the move:} e6 {which is very popular nowadays and the arising positions are rather unexplored and playable}) 3... cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6 5. Nc3 Bg7 {This is the starting position of the Accelerated Dragon} 6. Be3 ({I analyzed} 6. Nxc6) (6. Nb3) (6. Nde2) 6... Nf6 7. Bc4 (7. Nxc6 {This variation is not without venom, but I believe Black is doing fine after 7...Ng8. 7...Nd5 is also playable but risky.} bxc6 8. e5) 7... O-O 8. Bb3 {This is the absolute mainline. I decided to analyze everything here, but my main preferences are to three moves:} d6 {Classical approach, I believe that Black is doing fine here} (8... Re8 {The Dubov Variation, which I think is quite playable. I am looking forward to trying it my next games. This is probably my favorite response for Black}) (8... a5 {This tricky move, which perhaps didn't equalize fully, but contains a lot of venoms and White will be cautious not be worse quickly}) *

