{In the first lecture, White's deviation on the second move. Everything else besides the main moves 2.Nf3 and 2.Nc3} 1. e4 c5 2. c3 (2. b3 Nc6 $1 {Trying to get e5-d6 setup}) (2. d3 Nc6 3. g3 g6 4. Bg2 Bg7 5. f4 d6 6. Nf3 e6 7. O-O Nge7 8. c3 {Here I suggest the simple plan with b6-Ba6,Rc8 preparing d6-d5 break}) (2. f4 {Is well met by} d5) (2. g3 {is well met by} d5) (2. b4 {Against this gambit I am glad that I found an efficient approach} cxb4 3. a3 b3 $1) (2. Be2 {This sideline becomes popular recently. I suggest a very simple approach} Nc6 3. f4 d5 4. d3 {and then either} dxe4 ({or} 4... e6)) 2... d5 3. exd5 Qxd5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. d4 Nf6 {The so-called two knight system is very popular and It stays pretty good theoretically. Black is aiming to get a very good version of IQP} *

