1. e4 c5 2. Be2 {This move has become popular recently. White's idea is to play the Dutch defense with reversed colors. If Black chooses a setup with g6 then White will just continue with d3, f4, Nf3, 0-0, Qe1-h4, c3, etc...} Nc6 3. f4 d5 {I like this approach very much} 4. d3 (4. e5 {doesn't make any sense here}) 4... e6 {This is the move for those of you who don't want to exchange queens so early in the game. The setup is very simple: we want to continue with Bd6-Nge7, etc...} (4... dxe4 {This simple move solves all Black's problems. We enter an endgame where I believebelieve that Black can fight for an advantage. It is really simple to play this position} 5. dxe4 Qxd1+ 6. Bxd1 e6 $1 7. Nf3 b6 8. c3 Nf6 9. Ba4 {Looks more critical, but Black si just in time to protect everything.} (9. e5 Nd5 10. O-O Ba6 11. Ba4 Rc8 12. Re1 Be7 13. g3 O-O 14. Nbd2 Rfd8 $15 {All Black's pieces are well-placed and coordinated. White has some holes in his position. For example, the d3-square. Also, his c1-bishop is quite passive, and his a1-rook can't enter the game very easily. I believe that Black is simply slightly better here 0-1 (41) Bortnyk,O (2598)-Xiong,J (2709) Speed Chess Invitational Chess.com INT blitz 2020 (1.10)}) 9... Bb7 10. Ne5 Rc8 11. Nd2 Be7 12. g4 O-O 13. Bxc6 Bxc6 14. g5 Nd7 15. Nxc6 Rxc6 16. Nf3 f5 $1 {Very nice idea, which you need to remember} 17. exf5 (17. e5 b5 {[%cal Rd7b6,Rb6d5]}) 17... exf5 $15 {Here we have the e-file at our disposal and also the pawns on the queenside are at the same square as White bishop. ½- (38) ½ Piorun,K (2640)-Wojtaszek,R (2694) POL-ch Ekstraliga Rapid Final Bydgoszcz 2022 (6.1)}) 5. Nf3 Bd6 6. O-O Nge7 7. c3 (7. e5 {Just leads to the advanced structure, but Black already developed his minor pieces from the kingside. This "French" position type is more than good for Black} Bc7 8. c3 O-O 9. d4 cxd4 10. cxd4 Nf5 {The simplest plan is to start attacking the d4-pawn} 11. Bd3 Ncxd4 12. g4 Nxf3+ 13. Rxf3 Ne7 14. Rh3 g6 15. g5 Nf5 $17 {0-1 (30) Williams,S (2467)-Alsina Leal,D (2509) BCF-chT 2122 (4NCL) England 2021 (11.32)}) 7... f6 {We need to make this concession because we are planning to continue with Qc7 in the future.} 8. Be3 O-O 9. Nbd2 b6 10. Kh1 Qc7 11. g3 Bb7 12. Rc1 Rad8 $17 13. Qe1 Qd7 14. a3 a5 15. Rg1 a4 {An absolute model game for Black. He first wins some space on the queenside before starting any concrete actions} 16. Bf1 Bc7 17. Bg2 dxe4 (17... e5 $1 $17) 18. dxe4 Na5 19. Qe2 Qd3 {The endgame will be very hard for White due to his fixed queenside and the fact that White controls the open d-file} 20. Qf2 h6 21. h4 Qb5 22. Rb1 f5 23. e5 Nd5 24. Bf1 Qe8 25. Kh2 Bc6 26. Be2 Rd7 27. Rbd1 Qf7 28. Nb1 Rfd8 29. Bc1 b5 30. Be3 Nxe3 31. Qxe3 Nc4 32. Qc1 Bd5 33. Ne1 g5 $19 {When White's pieces are passive Black strikes on the kingside} 34. fxg5 Nxe5 35. Rf1 Kh7 36. Ng2 hxg5 37. hxg5 Rh8 38. Kg1 Kg8 39. Nf4 Rh1+ 40. Kf2 Rh2+ 41. Ke1 Bg2 42. Rxd7 Qxd7 43. Rg1 Nf3+ 44. Kf2 Bh3+ 45. Ng2 Nxg1 {0-1 Mihajlov,S (2381)-Demchenko,A (2610) EU-Cup 36th Struga 2021 (3.2)} *

