1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 e6 {This was the hardest part of the workshop for me. The arising positions here are so complex that it is tough to go deep into them. Still, I think I did a great job, and by studying the analyses and the model games, you will be ready to face Rossolimo.  White has several ways to continue:} 4. Bxc6 {Is very interesting and challenging. The arising structure is not easy to handle for both sides.} (4. O-O {Is another main line} Nge7 {White can choose between:} 5. d4 (5. Re1)) 4... bxc6 5. d3 {One piece of advice for everyone who will play this line. Study very carefully all Boris Gelfand's games here} *

