1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 e6 4. c3 {White doesn't want to lose time for castle and wants to proceed with d2-d4 as soon as possible. Black is at a crossroads; he can strike the centre immediately with d5 or first develop with Nge7. I prefer the second option} (4. Nc3 Nd4 $1 {Now we suddenly transpose to the 2.Nc3 variation, which we discussed earlier in the database.} (4... Nge7 {Black can stay in the Rossolimo} 5. O-O Qb6 6. Re1 Ng6 7. a4 Be7 8. e5 (8. Bxc6 {White needs to take the knight if he wants to play for an advantage. Otherwise, Nd4 will come soon} bxc6 (8... Qxc6 $2 {It is important to know that this move is not good due to:} 9. d4 cxd4 10. Nxd4 {with a good version of Open Sicilian}) 9. e5 $13) 8... O-O 9. d3 Nd4 $17 {0-1 (30) Tologontegin,S (2358)-Korobov,A (2683) Chess.com INT 2020}) 5. O-O a6 6. Bd3 {½-½ (60) Guseinov,G (2661)-Andreikin,D (2729) Chess.com INT 2023}) (4. d3 $2 {Has one obvious drawback and leads to trouble after:} Qa5+ $1 {White is forced to put the knight on c3} 5. Nc3 Nd4 $1 6. Bc4 (6. Nxd4 cxd4 $19 {[%csl Rc3]}) 6... b5 7. Bb3 (7. Nxd4 cxd4) 7... Nxb3 8. cxb3 $15 {[%cal Rc2b3]}) (4. b3 {Another trendy sideline} Nd4 (4... Nge7 {Gelfand tries this approach but doesn't equalize completely after:} 5. Bb2 a6 6. Bxc6 Nxc6 7. O-O b6 8. d4 cxd4 9. Nxd4 Bb7 10. c4 Be7 11. Nxc6 Bxc6 12. Qg4 Bf6 13. e5 h5 14. Qe2 Be7 15. Ba3 h4 {½-½ (63) Antipov,M (2584)-Gelfand,B (2676) Lichess.org INT 2020}) 5. Bd3 (5. Nxd4 cxd4 {[%cal Rd2d3]} 6. O-O Ne7 {White's structure loses flexibility} 7. c3 a6 8. Bd3 Nc6 9. Bb2 Bc5 10. Na3 O-O 11. Nc2 Ne5 12. Qe2 dxc3 13. dxc3 b5 {0-1 (66) Henderson de la Fuente,L (2459)-Zhigalko,S (2608) Budapest 2018}) 5... Ne7 6. Nxd4 cxd4 7. c3 Nc6 8. Bb2 Bc5 9. O-O O-O 10. b4 Bb6 11. Na3 d5 12. Qe2 dxc3 13. dxc3 Qh4 14. Nb5 Rd8 15. a4 a5 16. bxa5 Rxa5 17. c4 d4 18. e5 Bc5 19. f4 Nb4 20. Rf3 Nxd3 21. Qxd3 Qg4 22. Kh1 Bd7 23. h3 Qg6 24. Qxg6 hxg6 25. Rd3 Bc6 26. Nxd4 Rxa4 27. Rxa4 Bxa4 28. Rd2 Bc6 29. Nf3 Rxd2 30. Nxd2 Be3 31. Nb3 Bxf4 32. Kg1 Bg3 33. Bc3 Kh7 34. Bb2 g5 35. Na5 Be4 {0-1 (35) Gascon del Nogal,J (2460)-Ibarra Jerez,J (2563) Chess.com INT 2023}) (4. c4 {doesn't make any sense here} Nge7) 4... Nge7 (4... d5 $1 5. exd5 ({If} 5. d3 Bd7 $1 (5... Nge7 6. Qe2 a6 7. Ba4 b5 8. Bc2 Ng6 9. h4 d4 10. h5 Nge5 11. Nxe5 Nxe5 12. cxd4 cxd4 {[%csl Rc2][%cal Rf2f4]} 13. f4 Nc6 {[%cal Rc8b7,Ra8c8] 0-1 (61) Vasquez Schroder,R (2459)-Yilmaz,M (2630) Lichess.org INT 2021}) 6. O-O Nf6 7. Re1 Be7 8. Ba4 d4 9. e5 Nd5 10. c4 Nc7 {[%csl Rc7][%cal Rf7f5]} 11. Nbd2 O-O 12. Ne4 f5 13. exf6 gxf6 14. a3 a5 {½-½ (47) Chigaev,M (2542)-Gelfand,B (2620) Almaty 2022}) (5. Bxc6+ bxc6 6. Qa4 Bd7 7. d3 Ne7 8. Ne5 Ng6 9. Nxd7 (9. Nxg6 hxg6 {[%cal Rh8h2]}) 9... Qxd7 10. O-O Be7 11. f4 f5 (11... c4 $1) 12. e5 Qb7 {½-½ (24) Bernardo,D (2030)-Schebler,G (2391) Pattaya 2019}) 5... Qxd5 {this leads to some kind of Alapin favorable for Black. The b5-bishop is misplaced} 6. O-O Bd7 7. d3 a6 8. Ba4 Bd6 9. Bc2 Nf6 10. Nbd2 Bc7 11. Ne4 O-O-O (11... Nxe4 12. dxe4 Qh5 $11) 12. Bg5 h6 13. Bxf6 gxf6 14. Nxf6 {1-0 (65) Yu,Y (2729)-Chigaev,M (2617) Chess.com INT 2023}) 5. d4 cxd4 6. cxd4 a6 (6... d5 {Many players prefers not to include the a7-a6 move, because now Qb6 will come with tempo and the b5-bishop is quite often misplaced.} 7. e5 Nf5 8. Nc3 Bd7 9. O-O a6 10. Bxc6 Bxc6 11. Re1 Be7 $11 {Black doesn't have any problems here: 0-1 (41) Wagner,D (2584)-Xiong,J (2688) Chess.com INT 2022}) 7. Be2 (7. Ba4 {allows Black to win more tempis after:} d5 8. e5 Nf5 {[%cal Rc8d7,Rf8e7,Re8g8]} 9. Nc3 Bd7 {½-½ (59) Dos Santos,M (2457)-Szczepanski,Z (2524) ICCF email 2015}) 7... d5 8. e5 {The position resembles "Advanced French"} Qb6 9. Bd3 Bd7 10. Bc2 $6 {This move is not good, but it is hard to suggest anything better for White} Nb4 11. O-O Nxc2 12. Qxc2 Nf5 13. Be3 Rc8 {With an obvious advantage for Black} 14. Nc3 Bb4 15. a3 Bxc3 16. bxc3 O-O 17. g4 Nxe3 18. fxe3 f6 19. exf6 gxf6 20. g5 Bb5 21. Rf2 Qc7 22. gxf6 Rxf6 23. a4 Bc4 24. Rg2+ Kh8 25. Ne5 Rcf8 26. h3 Bf1 27. Rg3 Rf5 28. Re1 Qe7 29. e4 Qh4 30. Ree3 Rg5 31. Qh2 Bxh3 32. Rxg5 Rf1# *

