1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6 5. Nc3 Bg7 6. Be3 Nf6 7. Be2 O-O 8. O-O {There is a reason why White played Nb3 earlier. With this move order Black can show one of the main advantages of the Accelerated Dragon by playing d7-d5 in one move} d5 $1 9. exd5 Nb4 10. a3 $2 {already a mistake and Black is much better} (10. d6 Qxd6 11. Ndb5 Qb8 12. a4 Bf5 $17 {0-1 (52) Dolezal,C (2436)-Chatalbashev,B (2605) Benidorm 2008}) ({White should already think how to keep the balance} 10. Qd2 Nbxd5 11. Nxd5 Nxd5 12. Bg5 (12. Bh6 Bxh6 (12... e5 13. Bxg7 Kxg7 14. Nf3 Nf4 {0-1 (40) Lkhagvasuren,T (2355)-Chatalbashev,B (2535) Elista 1998}) 13. Qxh6 Qb6 14. Nb3 Bf5 15. Rfd1 Rad8 $15 {0-1 (60) Paleologu,V (2162)-Chatalbashev,B (2549) Lugano 2014}) 12... Nf6 $11) 10... Nbxd5 11. Qd2 Nxc3 12. bxc3 Nd5 $17 {I didn't play the best way, but I scored a quick win} 13. Rad1 Nxe3 14. Qxe3 Qa5 15. Qxe7 Qxc3 16. Nb5 Qxc2 17. Rc1 Qb2 18. f4 Be6 19. Bd3 Rad8 20. Rb1 Qd2 *

