1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Bg7 6. Be3 O-O 7. f3 {As we know, the most dangerous setup against Dragon is with 0-0-0, so logically, White can try to do the same here. Unfortunately for the first player, this move is simply not playable and Black enjoys a nice game after the typical} Nc6 8. Qd2 d5 9. exd5 Nxd5 10. Nxd5 (10. Nxc6 bxc6 11. Nxd5 cxd5 {You probably know that this position is good for Black, even If White has a tempo up and already castled, so now Black is simply better} 12. c3 Qa5 {0-1 (26) Schaffarth,M (2065)-Feygin,M (2515) Saarlouis 1998}) 10... Qxd5 11. Nxc6 Qxc6 12. O-O-O Bf5 13. Bd3 Rad8 14. Qe2 Bxd3 15. Rxd3 Qb5 $19 {After some complications, Nyzhnyk won the game: 0-1 (33) Wei,J (1918)-Nyzhnyk,I (2676) Cherry Hill 2021} *

