1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6 5. Nc3 Bg7 6. Be3 Nf6 7. Bc4 O-O 8. f3 {Doesn't work as well. Black easily equalizes after:} (8. O-O Nxe4 9. Nxe4 (9. Bxf7+ Rxf7 10. Nxe4 Bxd4 11. Bxd4 d5 12. Ng3 e5 13. Be3 d4 14. Bd2 {0-1 (14) Aleksic,N (2357)-Altini,N (2347) Campobasso 2013}) 9... d5 10. Nxc6 bxc6 11. Bd3 dxe4 12. Bxe4 Ba6 13. Qxd8 Rfxd8 {½-½ (39) Vocaturo,D (2617)-Lodici,L (2483) Premium Chess Arena INT 2020}) 8... Qb6 {[%cal Rb6b2,Rf6e4,Rf6g4] This multipurpose move works very well here as well} {Black needs to be very accurate, not to lose on the spot here} 9. Bb3 (9. Ncb5 $4 a6 $19) (9. Nxc6 $4 Qxe3+ $19) (9. Nf5 $4 $19 Qxb2) (9. Bb5 $2 Nxe4 10. Nd5 Qa5+ 11. c3 Nf6 $17) (9. O-O $2 Qxb2 10. Ndb5 Qb4 11. Qe2 Qa5 $19) (9. Na4 Qb4+) (9. a3 e6 $17) (9. Qd2 $2 Nxe4 10. fxe4 (10. Nxe4 Bxd4 $17) 10... Bxd4 $17) 9... Nxe4 (9... Ng4 $1 10. fxg4 (10. Nd5 {loses material after:} Nxe3 11. Nxb6 Nxd1 12. Nxa8 Nxb2 {0-1 (48) Panda,V (2069)-Krysa,L (2531) Chess.com INT 2020}) 10... Bxd4 11. Nd5 (11. Bxd4 Qxd4 12. Qxd4 Nxd4 $11 {is just equal}) 11... Qa5+ 12. Bd2 Qd8 13. c3 Bg7 14. O-O e6 $15 15. Nf4 b6 $15 {Black is better he will soon install the knight on e5 0-1 (91) Oparin,G (2674)-So,W (2778) Chess.com INT 2022}) 10. Nd5 Qa5+ 11. c3 Nc5 12. Nxc6 dxc6 13. Nxe7+ $11 *[Event "Campobasso op 20th"]
