1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 g6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Bg7 6. Be3 Nf6 7. Bc4 O-O ({There is a move} 7... Qa5 {which forces White to go for 0-0} 8. O-O O-O 9. Bb3 d6 {we get one of the main theoretical positions. Where White can choose between 10.h3 or 10.Nd5. I don't like this position very much, because it is quite passive, but it deserves attention.} 10. Nd5 Re8 11. Nxf6+ Bxf6 12. c3 Bd7 13. f4 Nxd4 14. cxd4 (14. Bxd4 Bxd4+ 15. Qxd4 Qc5 16. Qxc5 dxc5 17. Kf2 e5) 14... e6 15. e5 Bg7 $11) 8. Bb3 {This is the real crossroad of the line. Black has many options here. I will mention them one by one.} d5 {This move has become popular recently. Black tries to equalize by force. This variation is possible, but didn't equalize completely.} (8... Na5 $2 {Is a well-known mistake Fischer refuted 50 years ago} 9. e5 Ne8 10. Bxf7+ $1 Kxf7 (10... Rxf7 11. Ne6 {traps the queen}) 11. Ne6 $3 dxe6 (11... Kxe6 12. Qd5+ Kf5 13. g4+ Kxg4 14. Rg1+ $18 {With mate to follow}) 12. Qxd8 $18) (8... a6 {This is a nice new idea suggested in some books recently. Black wants to play Nc7 followed by Na5. This could be a great surprise weapon.} 9. f3 (9. O-O) 9... d6 10. Qd2 Na5 11. Bh6 Bxh6 12. Qxh6 e5 13. Nde2 b5 14. Qd2 b4 15. Na4 Nxb3 16. axb3 a5 17. O-O-O Ra6 18. h4 Be6 19. h5 Qe7 {0-1 (48) Hou,Y (2603)-Nakamura,H (2769) Wijk aan Zee 2013}) (8... Qa5) 9. exd5 Na5 {It is not so simple to win the pawn back. White tried different moves here:} 10. Qf3 $5 (10. O-O Nxb3 11. Nxb3 b6 12. d6 (12. Qd2 Bb7 13. Rad1 Qc7 14. Bf4 Qc4 15. Rfe1 Rfd8 $11 {½-½ (68) Negi,P (2664)-Hou,Y (2683) Saint Louis 2015}) 12... e6 (12... Qxd6 13. Qxd6 exd6 14. Rfe1 Bf5 15. Nd4 $14) 13. Qf3 Rb8 14. Rad1 (14. Rfd1 $5 Bb7 15. Qh3 Rc8 16. Bd4 $14 {1-0 (34) Vachier Lagrave,M (2796)-Gelfand,B (2719) Palma de Mallorca 2017}) 14... Bb7 15. Qh3 Nd5 16. Nxd5 Bxd5 17. Bd4 Bxd4 18. Rxd4 Rc8 19. Qh6 $16 {½-½ (33) Adhiban,B (2670)-Gelfand,B (2737) Douglas 2017}) (10. Qd2 Nxb3 11. Nxb3 b5 $1 12. Nxb5 (12. O-O-O $6 b4 13. Na4 Bf5 $1 $17 {[%csl Rc2]}) 12... Qxd5 $1 13. Qxd5 Nxd5 14. Bd4 Bh6 15. O-O Bf5 16. c4 Bd3 17. cxd5 Bxb5 {1-0 (68) Aravindh,C (2633)-Theodorou,N (2591) Dubai 2023}) (10. Nde2 a6 11. O-O b5 12. a3 Nxb3 (12... Bb7 $5) 13. cxb3 Bb7 14. Nf4 Qd7 15. Qd2 Qf5 $15 {[%cal Ra8d8]}) 10... Nxb3 (10... Bg4 11. Qg3 Bh5 $5) 11. axb3 Bg4 12. Qg3 Bh5 13. d6 Ng4 $1 14. O-O-O (14. O-O Be5 15. f4 Bxd6 16. h3 Nxe3 17. Qxe3 Bc5 18. Ra4 b5 19. Ncxb5 Qb6 20. Na3 Rfd8 21. c3 Qxb3 22. Rc4 Bxd4 23. Rxd4 Rxd4 (23... Qxb2 $11 {[%cal Rb2e2]}) 24. Qxd4 $14 {0-1 (89) Perpinya Rofes,L (2366)-Grigoryan,K (2570) Badalona 2017}) (14. dxe7 Qxe7 15. O-O Rfe8 16. Nd5 Qc5) (14. h3 Nxe3 15. fxe3 a6 16. Qh4 (16. O-O e5 $11) 16... e5 17. Qxd8 Raxd8 18. Ne6 fxe6 19. g4 Rf3 20. Ke2 Rxh3 21. gxh5 Rxh1 22. Rxh1 Rxd6 {1-0 (47) Van Foreest,J (2680)-Gelfand,B (2678) Malmo 2023}) 14... Qa5 15. dxe7 Rfe8 16. Qd6 (16. Rde1 Rxe7 17. Kb1 Rae8 18. h3 Nxe3 19. fxe3 g5 $44) 16... Be5 $2 (16... Nxe3 17. fxe3 Bxd1 18. Rxd1 Be5 19. Qd7 Qa1+ 20. Kd2 Qxb2 21. Nd5 $13) 17. Qd5 Qc7 (17... Qxd5 18. Nxd5 Nxe3 19. fxe3 Bxd1 20. Rxd1 $13) 18. Rd3 $14 Rxe7 19. h3 Nxe3 20. fxe3 g5 21. Nf5 Re6 22. Ne4 Bg6 23. g4 Rae8 24. Nxg5 Rc6 25. c3 Bxc3 26. bxc3 Rxc3+ 27. Rxc3 Qxc3+ 28. Kb1 Qxe3 29. Nf3 Rc8 30. Ne5 Qe2 31. Rd1 Qc2+ 32. Ka1 Rf8 33. Qd4 Qxb3 34. Ne7+ Kg7 35. N5xg6+ f6 36. Nxf8 {1-0 (36) Ponomariov,R (2709)-Gelfand,B (2743) Tashkent 2016} *

